      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Bruce Rogers (1870-1957) was an American typographer and type designer.  He was known for his "classical" style of design, favoring typefaces such as Caslon and Centaur, the latter of which he designed himself.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Bruce Rogers Correspondence</emph> consists of a signed, handwritten letter dated 7 February 1900 on the letterhead of Houghton, Mifflin Company, Publishers, from the book designer Bruce Rogers to a Mr. Vincent.  The letter discusses Rogers' design for Vincent's book.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
